title: Baby bumps steal spotlight at Carji
text:
Jimmy and Nadia Bartel. Picture: NIGEL HALLETT Source: News Corp Australia 
EXPECTING mum Renee Enright mastered comfort and style on the Carji Greeves Medal red carpet tonight. 
The fashionable Geelong stylist, who will welcome her second child into the world with husband Corey next year, stepped out in a white Dion Lee silk blouse atop a knee-length white skirt with front split feature from the same designer. Renee Enright white Dion Lee silk blouse. atop with a knee-length white skirt. Picture: Nigel Hallett Source: News Corp Australia 
Nude Tony Bianco heels and a while Olga Berg clutch completed the look. 
Renee said she purposely kept her outfit simple and no-fuss for the Cats awards night at Crown Palladium in Melbourne. 
“Comfort is key for me with an expanding waist line,” she said. 
Nadia Bartel’s prominent baby bump was tucked under a black long-sleeve Misha Collection dress with signature cut-out detail on the chest and styled with Giuseppe Zanotti patent-leather heels and a black quilted YSL clutch. 
The fashion blogger, expecting her first child with husband Jimmy next month, admitted it was a challenge to find the perfect piece. 
CHECK OUT OUR RED CARPET PICTURE GALLERY 
“Being this pregnant makes it hard to find anything that actually fits,” she laughed. 
After flaunting a stunning red frock at the Brownlow, Emma Clapham accompanied fiance Tom Hawkins in a black long-sleeve, low-cut dress by Sheike. 
Demi Miles, partner of Mitch Duncan, wore a navy halter neck Nicholas number from Green with Envy, matched with nude lace-up Tony Bianco heels and a YSL clutch from The Style Secret. 
“It’s not something I would usually wear,” Miles said. 
“It’s completely different to my normal style, however, I am excited to be stepping outside the box.” 
Brit Davis, girlfriend of captain Joel Selwood, sparkled in a Manning Cartell ensemble. 
Cam Guthrie, who invited his mum to the Brownlow last week, was this time accompanied by his girlfriend Lauren Bumbers. 
All of the Cats players were dressed by Godwin Charli.
